2. 🗄️ SQL Validation Scripts

tests/sql/validation_queries.sql

-- Dairy Management System - SQL Validation Queries
-- Run these after API operations to verify database consistency

-- 1. Farmer Data Validation
SELECT 
    'Farmer Validation' as test_category,
    COUNT(*) as total_farmers,
    COUNT(DISTINCT code) as unique_codes,
    COUNT(CASE WHEN kyc_status = 'verified' THEN 1 END) as verified_farmers,
    COUNT(CASE WHEN bank_account_number IS NOT NULL THEN 1 END) as farmers_with_bank
FROM dairy.farmer;

-- 2. Collection Data Integrity
SELECT 
    'Collection Validation' as test_category,
    COUNT(*) as total_collections,
    COUNT(DISTINCT slip_number) as unique_slips,
    SUM(qty_ltr) as total_milk_collected,
    AVG(fat_pct) as avg_fat_percentage,
    AVG(snf_pct) as avg_snf_percentage,
    COUNT(CASE WHEN fat_pct > 15 OR fat_pct < 0 THEN 1 END) as invalid_fat_records,
    COUNT(CASE WHEN snf_pct > 15 OR snf_pct < 0 THEN 1 END) as invalid_snf_records
FROM dairy.milk_collection;

-- 3. Payment Cycle Validation
SELECT 
    pc.id as cycle_id,
    pc.cycle_name,
    pc.status,
    pc.total_farmers,
    pc.total_amount,
    COUNT(pcd.id) as actual_farmer_count,
    SUM(pcd.final_amount) as calculated_total,
    ABS(pc.total_amount - SUM(pcd.final_amount)) as amount_difference
FROM dairy.payment_cycles pc
LEFT JOIN dairy.payment_cycle_details pcd ON pc.id = pcd.cycle_id
GROUP BY pc.id, pc.cycle_name, pc.status, pc.total_farmers, pc.total_amount
HAVING ABS(pc.total_amount - COALESCE(SUM(pcd.final_amount), 0)) > 0.01;

-- 4. Duplicate Collection Check
SELECT 
    farmer_id,
    shift_id,
    date,
    COUNT(*) as duplicate_count
FROM dairy.milk_collection
GROUP BY farmer_id, shift_id, date
HAVING COUNT(*) > 1;

-- 5. Rate Engine Validation
SELECT 
    mc.id,
    mc.qty_ltr,
    mc.fat_pct,
    mc.snf_pct,
    mc.price_per_ltr,
    mc.due_amt,
    (mc.qty_ltr * mc.price_per_ltr) as calculated_amount,
    ABS(mc.due_amt - (mc.qty_ltr * mc.price_per_ltr)) as amount_difference
FROM dairy.milk_collection mc
WHERE ABS(mc.due_amt - (mc.qty_ltr * mc.price_per_ltr)) > 0.01;

-- 6. POS Order Validation
SELECT 
    po.id,
    po.total_amount,
    SUM(poi.amount) as items_total,
    po.gst_amount,
    po.final_amount,
    ABS(po.total_amount - SUM(poi.amount)) as items_difference
FROM dairy.pos_orders po
LEFT JOIN dairy.pos_order_items poi ON po.id = poi.order_id
GROUP BY po.id, po.total_amount, po.gst_amount, po.final_amount
HAVING ABS(po.total_amount - COALESCE(SUM(poi.amount), 0)) > 0.01;

-- 7. Bank Account Validation
SELECT 
    'Bank Account Validation' as test_category,
    COUNT(CASE WHEN bank_account_number ~ '^[0-9]{9,18}$' THEN 1 END) as valid_account_numbers,
    COUNT(CASE WHEN bank_ifsc_code ~ '^[A-Z]{4}0[A-Z0-9]{6}$' THEN 1 END) as valid_ifsc_codes,
    COUNT(*) as total_farmers_with_bank_details
FROM dairy.farmer
WHERE bank_account_number IS NOT NULL;

-- 8. Audit Trail Validation
SELECT 
    DATE(timestamp) as audit_date,
    action,
    entity,
    COUNT(*) as operation_count
FROM dairy.audit_log
WHERE timestamp >= CURRENT_DATE - INTERVAL '7 days'
GROUP BY DATE(timestamp), action, entity
ORDER BY audit_date DESC, operation_count DESC;

-- 9. System Alerts Check
SELECT 
    alert_type,
    severity,
    COUNT(*) as alert_count,
    COUNT(CASE WHEN is_resolved = false THEN 1 END) as unresolved_count
FROM dairy.system_alerts
WHERE created_at >= CURRENT_DATE - INTERVAL '24 hours'
GROUP BY alert_type, severity
ORDER BY severity DESC, unresolved_count DESC;

-- 10. Performance Metrics
SELECT 
    'Performance Metrics' as test_category,
    (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM dairy.milk_collection WHERE date = CURRENT_DATE) as todays_collections,
    (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM dairy.pos_orders WHERE DATE(created_at) = CURRENT_DATE) as todays_pos_orders,
    (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM dairy.payment_cycles WHERE status = 'active') as active_cycles,
    (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM dairy.system_alerts WHERE is_resolved = false) as unresolved_alerts;

6. 🔒 Security Test Scripts

tests/security/security-tests.js

const axios = require('axios');

const BASE_URL = 'https://your-api.render.com';

// SQL Injection Tests
const sqlInjectionPayloads = [
  "'; DROP TABLE farmers; --",
  "' OR '1'='1",
  "'; UPDATE farmers SET name='HACKED'; --",
  "' UNION SELECT * FROM users; --"
];

async function testSqlInjection() {
  console.log('🔍 Testing SQL Injection...');
  
  for (const payload of sqlInjectionPayloads) {
    try {
      const response = await axios.get(`${BASE_URL}/api/farmers?search=${encodeURIComponent(payload)}`);
      
      if (response.status === 500 || 
          response.data.includes('syntax error') || 
          response.data.includes('DROP TABLE')) {
        console.log(`❌ SQL Injection vulnerability found with payload: ${payload}`);
      } else {
        console.log(`✅ SQL Injection prevented for payload: ${payload}`);
      }
    } catch (error) {
      console.log(`✅ SQL Injection blocked: ${error.response?.status}`);
    }
  }
}

// JWT Security Tests
async function testJwtSecurity() {
  console.log('🔐 Testing JWT Security...');
  
  const invalidTokens = [
    'invalid.jwt.token',
    'eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJzdWIiOiIxMjM0NTY3ODkwIiwibmFtZSI6IkpvaG4gRG9lIiwiaWF0IjoxNTE2MjM5MDIyfQ.SflKxwRJSMeKKF2QT4fwpMeJf36POk6yJV_adQssw5c',
    '',
    'Bearer malformed'
  ];

  for (const token of invalidTokens) {
    try {
      const response = await axios.get(`${BASE_URL}/api/farmers`, {
        headers: { Authorization: `Bearer ${token}` }
      });
      
      if (response.status === 200) {
        console.log(`❌ Unauthorized access allowed with token: ${token}`);
      }
    } catch (error) {
      if (error.response?.status === 401) {
        console.log(`✅ Unauthorized access blocked for invalid token`);
      }
    }
  }
}

// XSS Tests
async function testXssPrevention() {
  console.log('🛡️ Testing XSS Prevention...');
  
  const xssPayloads = [
    '<script>alert("XSS")</script>',
    '"><script>alert("XSS")</script>',
    'javascript:alert("XSS")',
    '<img src=x onerror=alert("XSS")>'
  ];

  for (const payload of xssPayloads) {
    try {
      const response = await axios.post(`${BASE_URL}/api/farmers`, {
        name: payload,
        code: 'XSS001',
        contact: '9876543210'
      });
      
      if (response.data.name === payload) {
        console.log(`❌ XSS vulnerability: payload stored as-is`);
      } else {
        console.log(`✅ XSS prevented: payload sanitized`);
      }
    } catch (error) {
      console.log(`✅ XSS blocked: ${error.response?.status}`);
    }
  }
}

// Run all security tests
async function runSecurityTests() {
  await testSqlInjection();
  await testJwtSecurity();
  await testXssPrevention();
}

module.exports = { runSecurityTests };

7. 📊 Performance Monitoring Script

tests/performance/performance-monitor.js

const axios = require('axios');
const fs = require('fs');

class PerformanceMonitor {
  constructor(baseUrl) {
    this.baseUrl = baseUrl;
    this.results = [];
  }

  async measureEndpoint(name, method, url, data = null) {
    const startTime = Date.now();
    
    try {
      const config = {
        method,
        url: `${this.baseUrl}${url}`,
        timeout: 10000
      };
      
      if (data) config.data = data;
      
      const response = await axios(config);
      const endTime = Date.now();
      
      this.results.push({
        endpoint: name,
        method,
        url,
        responseTime: endTime - startTime,
        status: response.status,
        success: true,
        timestamp: new Date().toISOString()
      });
      
      return response;
    } catch (error) {
      const endTime = Date.now();
      
      this.results.push({
        endpoint: name,
        method,
        url,
        responseTime: endTime - startTime,
        status: error.response?.status || 0,
        success: false,
        error: error.message,
        timestamp: new Date().toISOString()
      });
      
      throw error;
    }
  }

  async runPerformanceTests() {
    console.log('🚀 Starting Performance Tests...');

    // Test critical endpoints
    const tests = [
      { name: 'Get Farmers', method: 'GET', url: '/api/farmers' },
      { name: 'Get Collections', method: 'GET', url: '/api/collections' },
      { name: 'Create Collection', method: 'POST', url: '/api/collections', 
        data: {
          farmerId: 1,
          shiftId: 1,
          date: '2025-01-09',
          quantity: 25.5,
          fatPercentage: 4.2,
          snfPercentage: 8.8,
          rate: 52.50,
          amount: 1338.75
        }
      },
      { name: 'Dashboard KPIs', method: 'GET', url: '/api/feedback-features/analytics/dashboard-kpis' },
      { name: 'Create POS Order', method: 'POST', url: '/api/pos/orders',
        data: {
          customerId: 1,
          items: [{ productId: 1, quantity: 2, unitPrice: 60, amount: 120 }],
          totalAmount: 120,
          paymentMethod: 'UPI'
        }
      }
    ];

    // Run each test multiple times
    for (const test of tests) {
      console.log(`Testing ${test.name}...`);
      
      for (let i = 0; i < 10; i++) {
        try {
          await this.measureEndpoint(test.name, test.method, test.url, test.data);
          await new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, 100)); // 100ms delay
        } catch (error) {
          console.log(`❌ ${test.name} failed: ${error.message}`);
        }
      }
    }

    this.generateReport();
  }

  generateReport() {
    const report = {
      summary: this.generateSummary(),
      details: this.results,
      timestamp: new Date().toISOString()
    };

    // Save to file
    fs.writeFileSync('performance-report.json', JSON.stringify(report, null, 2));
    
    console.log('\n📊 Performance Test Results:');
    console.log('================================');
    
    Object.entries(report.summary).forEach(([endpoint, stats]) => {
      console.log(`${endpoint}:`);
      console.log(`  Average Response Time: ${stats.avgResponseTime}ms`);
      console.log(`  Success Rate: ${stats.successRate}%`);
      console.log(`  Min/Max: ${stats.minResponseTime}ms / ${stats.maxResponseTime}ms`);
      console.log('');
    });
  }

  generateSummary() {
    const summary = {};
    
    // Group by endpoint
    const grouped = this.results.reduce((acc, result) => {
      if (!acc[result.endpoint]) acc[result.endpoint] = [];
      acc[result.endpoint].push(result);
      return acc;
    }, {});

    Object.entries(grouped).forEach(([endpoint, results]) => {
      const responseTimes = results.map(r => r.responseTime);
      const successCount = results.filter(r => r.success).length;
      
      summary[endpoint] = {
        totalRequests: results.length,
        successCount,
        successRate: Math.round((successCount / results.length) * 100),
        avgResponseTime: Math.round(responseTimes.reduce((a, b) => a + b, 0) / responseTimes.length),
        minResponseTime: Math.min(...responseTimes),
        maxResponseTime: Math.max(...responseTimes)
      };
    });

    return summary;
  }
}

module.exports = PerformanceMonitor;

#!/bin/bash

echo "🧪 Starting Comprehensive QA Test Suite"
echo "========================================"

# Colors for output
RED='\033[0;31m'
GREEN='\033[0;32m'
YELLOW='\033[1;33m'
NC='\033[0m' # No Color

# Test results
UNIT_TESTS_PASSED=false
API_TESTS_PASSED=false
E2E_TESTS_PASSED=false
SECURITY_TESTS_PASSED=false
PERFORMANCE_TESTS_PASSED=false

# 1. Unit Tests
echo -e "${YELLOW}Running Unit Tests...${NC}"
if dotnet test --verbosity normal; then
    echo -e "${GREEN}✅ Unit Tests Passed${NC}"
    UNIT_TESTS_PASSED=true
else
    echo -e "${RED}❌ Unit Tests Failed${NC}"
fi

# 2. API Tests with Newman
echo -e "${YELLOW}Running API Tests...${NC}"
if newman run tests/postman/dairy-management-tests.json \
    --environment tests/postman/test-environment.json \
    --reporters cli; then
    echo -e "${GREEN}✅ API Tests Passed${NC}"
    API_TESTS_PASSED=true
else
    echo -e "${RED}❌ API Tests Failed${NC}"
fi

# 3. E2E Tests with Playwright
echo -e "${YELLOW}Running E2E Tests...${NC}"
if npx playwright test; then
    echo -e "${GREEN}✅ E2E Tests Passed${NC}"
    E2E_TESTS_PASSED=true
else
    echo -e "${RED}❌ E2E Tests Failed${NC}"
fi

# 4. Security Tests
echo -e "${YELLOW}Running Security Tests...${NC}"
if node tests/security/security-tests.js; then
    echo -e "${GREEN}✅ Security Tests Passed${NC}"
    SECURITY_TESTS_PASSED=true
else
    echo -e "${RED}❌ Security Tests Failed${NC}"
fi

# 5. Performance Tests
echo -e "${YELLOW}Running Performance Tests...${NC}"
if node tests/performance/performance-monitor.js; then
    echo -e "${GREEN}✅ Performance Tests Passed${NC}"
    PERFORMANCE_TESTS_PASSED=true
else
    echo -e "${RED}❌ Performance Tests Failed${NC}"
fi

# Summary
echo ""
echo "🏁 Test Execution Summary"
echo "========================="
echo -e "Unit Tests: $([ "$UNIT_TESTS_PASSED" = true ] && echo "${GREEN}PASSED${NC}" || echo "${RED}FAILED${NC}")"
echo -e "API Tests: $([ "$API_TESTS_PASSED" = true ] && echo "${GREEN}PASSED${NC}" || echo "${RED}FAILED${NC}")"
echo -e "E2E Tests: $([ "$E2E_TESTS_PASSED" = true ] && echo "${GREEN}PASSED${NC}" || echo "${RED}FAILED${NC}")"
echo -e "Security Tests: $([ "$SECURITY_TESTS_PASSED" = true ] && echo "${GREEN}PASSED${NC}" || echo "${RED}FAILED${NC}")"
echo -e "Performance Tests: $([ "$PERFORMANCE_TESTS_PASSED" = true ] && echo "${GREEN}PASSED${NC}" || echo "${RED}FAILED${NC}")"

# Exit with error if any tests failed
if [ "$UNIT_TESTS_PASSED" = true ] && [ "$API_TESTS_PASSED" = true ] && [ "$E2E_TESTS_PASSED" = true ] && [ "$SECURITY_TESTS_PASSED" = true ] && [ "$PERFORMANCE_TESTS_PASSED" = true ]; then
    echo -e "\n${GREEN}🎉 All Tests Passed!${NC}"
    exit 0
else
    echo -e "\n${RED}💥 Some Tests Failed!${NC}"
    exit 1
fi

10. 📊 Test Report Generator

scripts/generate-test-report.js

const fs = require('fs');
const path = require('path');

class TestReportGenerator {
  constructor() {
    this.results = {
      unit: null,
      api: null,
      e2e: null,
      security: null,
      performance: null
    };
  }

  loadResults() {
    // Load unit test results
    try {
      const unitResults = fs.readFileSync('TestResults/coverage.json', 'utf8');
      this.results.unit = JSON.parse(unitResults);
    } catch (e) {
      console.log('Unit test results not found');
    }

    // Load API test results
    try {
      const apiResults = fs.readFileSync('newman-report.json', 'utf8');
      this.results.api = JSON.parse(apiResults);
    } catch (e) {
      console.log('API test results not found');
    }

    // Load performance results
    try {
      const perfResults = fs.readFileSync('performance-report.json', 'utf8');
      this.results.performance = JSON.parse(perfResults);
    } catch (e) {
      console.log('Performance test results not found');
    }
  }

  generateHtmlReport() {
    const html = `
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Dairy Management System - QA Test Report</title>
    <style>
        body { font-family: Arial, sans-serif; margin: 20px; }
        .header { background: #2c3e50; color: white; padding: 20px; border-radius: 5px; }
        .section { margin: 20px 0; padding: 15px; border: 1px solid #ddd; border-radius: 5px; }
        .pass { color: #27ae60; }
        .fail { color: #e74c3c; }
        .warning { color: #f39c12; }
        table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 10px 0; }
        th, td { border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 8px; text-align: left; }
        th { background-color: #f2f2f2; }
        .metric { display: inline-block; margin: 10px; padding: 15px; background: #ecf0f1; border-radius: 5px; }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="header">
        <h1>🧪 Dairy Management System - QA Test Report</h1>
        <p>Generated on: ${new Date().toLocaleString()}</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>📊 Test Summary</h2>
        <div class="metric">
            <strong>Unit Tests</strong><br>
            Status: <span class="${this.results.unit ? 'pass' : 'fail'}">
                ${this.results.unit ? 'PASSED' : 'NOT RUN'}
            </span>
        </div>
        <div class="metric">
            <strong>API Tests</strong><br>
            Status: <span class="${this.results.api ? 'pass' : 'fail'}">
                ${this.results.api ? 'PASSED' : 'NOT RUN'}
            </span>
        </div>
        <div class="metric">
            <strong>Performance Tests</strong><br>
            Status: <span class="${this.results.performance ? 'pass' : 'fail'}">
                ${this.results.performance ? 'COMPLETED' : 'NOT RUN'}
            </span>
        </div>
    </div>

    ${this.generatePerformanceSection()}
    ${this.generateApiTestSection()}
    ${this.generateRecommendationsSection()}

</body>
</html>`;

    fs.writeFileSync('test-report.html', html);
    console.log('✅ Test report generated: test-report.html');
  }

  generatePerformanceSection() {
    if (!this.results.performance) return '';

    const summary = this.results.performance.summary;
    let tableRows = '';

    Object.entries(summary).forEach(([endpoint, stats]) => {
      const status = stats.avgResponseTime < 1000 ? 'pass' : 
                    stats.avgResponseTime < 2000 ? 'warning' : 'fail';
      
      tableRows += `
        <tr>
            <td>${endpoint}</td>
            <td class="${status}">${stats.avgResponseTime}ms</td>
            <td>${stats.successRate}%</td>
            <td>${stats.totalRequests}</td>
        </tr>`;
    });

    return `
    <div class="section">
        <h2>🚀 Performance Test Results</h2>
        <table>
            <tr>
                <th>Endpoint</th>
                <th>Avg Response Time</th>
                <th>Success Rate</th>
                <th>Total Requests</th>
            </tr>
            ${tableRows}
        </table>
    </div>`;
  }

  generateApiTestSection() {
    if (!this.results.api) return '';

    return `
    <div class="section">
        <h2>🔌 API Test Results</h2>
        <p>Total Requests: ${this.results.api.run?.stats?.requests?.total || 'N/A'}</p>
        <p>Failed Requests: ${this.results.api.run?.stats?.requests?.failed || 'N/A'}</p>
        <p>Total Assertions: ${this.results.api.run?.stats?.assertions?.total || 'N/A'}</p>
        <p>Failed Assertions: ${this.results.api.run?.stats?.assertions?.failed || 'N/A'}</p>
    </div>`;
  }

  generateRecommendationsSection() {
    return `
    <div class="section">
        <h2>💡 Recommendations</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Performance:</strong> Endpoints with >2s response time need optimization</li>
            <li><strong>Security:</strong> Ensure all SQL injection tests pass</li>
            <li><strong>Reliability:</strong> Maintain >99% success rate for critical APIs</li>
            <li><strong>Monitoring:</strong> Set up alerts for response times >1s</li>
            <li><strong>Load Testing:</strong> Test with 500+ concurrent users regularly</li>
        </ul>
    </div>`;
  }
}

// Generate report
const generator = new TestReportGenerator();
generator.loadResults();
generator.generateHtmlReport();
